I20050118-1015

* I did a "Replace With > Latest from HEAD" on a project but nothing appeared 
to happen.
* Found this trace in my log
* CVS operations seemed to be dead at this point
* Restarting the workspace solved the problem

!ENTRY org.eclipse.team.cvs.core 4 0 2005-01-20 08:37:45.375
!MESSAGE I/O exception occurred: Read end dead
!STACK 0
java.io.IOException: Read end dead
	at java.io.PipedInputStream.receive(PipedInputStream.java:153)
	at java.io.PipedOutputStream.write(PipedOutputStream.java:118)
	at java.io.FilterOutputStream.write(FilterOutputStream.java:75)
	at java.io.FilterOutputStream.write(FilterOutputStream.java:123)
	at java.io.BufferedOutputStream.flushBuffer
(BufferedOutputStream.java:86)
	at java.io.BufferedOutputStream.write(BufferedOutputStream.java:130)
	at 
org.eclipse.team.internal.core.streams.TimeoutOutputStream.writeUntilDone
(TimeoutOutputStream.java:260)
	at org.eclipse.team.internal.core.streams.TimeoutOutputStream.runThread
(TimeoutOutputStream.java:195)
	at org.eclipse.team.internal.core.streams.TimeoutOutputStream.access$0
(TimeoutOutputStream.java:193)
	at org.eclipse.team.internal.core.streams.TimeoutOutputStream$1.run
(TimeoutOutputStream.java:66)
	at java.lang.Thread.run(Thread.java:813)

In the past I have seen strange exceptions from PipedInputStream. It is used 
by the Jsh SSH2 client that is usd by our SSH2 plugin. I'm not sure why this 
would bring down the Jsh client though.
*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 88869 ***
